Constructor & Destructor Documentation

cQueue::Iterator::Iterator (  const cQueue &  q,
bool  athead = true
)  [inline]
 

Constructor.

Iterator will walk on the queue passed as argument. The current object will be the first (if athead==true) or the last (athead==false) object in the queue.

cObject* cQueue::Iterator::operator++ (  int   )  [inline]
 

Returns the current object, then moves the iterator to the next item.

If the iterator has reached either end of the queue, nothing happens; you have to call init() again to restart iterating.

cObject* cQueue::Iterator::operator-- (  int   )  [inline]
 

Returns the current object, then moves the iterator to the previous item.

If the iterator has reached either end of the queue, nothing happens; you have to call init() again to restart iterating.
